webpackJsonp([72253887401119],{8357:function(a,e){a.exports={pathContext:{group:[{node:{fields:{title:"Emergency Aid for Katrina at the German Red Cross",date:"03 Sep 2005",slug:"/2005-09-03-emergency-aid-for-katrina-at-the-german-red-cross/",tags:"Y2005"},html:'<p>I didn\'t notice it a couple of days ago, but now you can <a href="http://drk.de/spenden/index.html" title="Spende an das Deutsche Rote Kreuz">donate online for "emergency aid USA" at the German Red Cross</a>. The donations are tax-deductible in Germany and you can pay by German bank transfer.</p>'},next:{fields:{title:"Mac in Mac",date:"27 Aug 2005",slug:"/2005-08-27-mac-in-mac/"}},previous:{fields:{title:"A Recipe for Waffles",date:"04 Sep 2005",slug:"/2005-09-04-a-recipe-for-waffles/"}}},{node:{fields:{title:"Mac in Mac",date:"27 Aug 2005",slug:"/2005-08-27-mac-in-mac/",tags:"Y2005"},html:'<p><img src="http://www.papascott.de/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2005/08/macmini.jpg" border="0" height="64" width="120" alt="macmini.jpg" align="right" /> On vacation I bought an iPod Shuffle. I couldn\'t plug it into my old PowerBook, so I had to get a Mac Mini <a href="http://www.cyberport.de/webshop/?DEEP=1005-129">(1.42 GHz / Combo Drive)</a>. </p>\n<p>Seriously \'santana\' (as in <a href="http://sports.yahoo.com/mlbpa/players/6441">Johan</a>) will be a nice companion to the 500 MHz PowerBook <a href="http://www.amazon.de/exec/obidos/redirect?link_code=ur2&amp;camp=1638&amp;tag=papascott-21&amp;creative=6742&amp;path=ASIN%2F0393324818">\'moneyball\'</a>. It has some amenities that moneyball lacks, and is small enough to move around the house if I want to use it upstairs. Managing music will be easier with a single machine for both Slimserver and iTunes (syncing an iPod via 802.11b is a pain). And thanks to <a href="http://www.redstonesoftware.com/vnc.html" title="VNC">OSXvnc</a> I don\'t even have to sit in front of santana to use it.</p>\n<p><img src="http://www.papascott.de/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2005/08/macinmac.png" border="0" height="307" width="461" alt="macinmac.png" /></p>\n<p>Setting up santana was pretty boring. Just plug in a mouse and keyboard (PC keyboard works just fine) and it works.</p>'},next:{fields:{title:"Wahl-O-Mat",date:"26 Aug 2005",slug:"/2005-08-26-wahl-o-mat/"}},previous:{fields:{title:"Emergency Aid for Katrina at the German Red Cross",date:"03 Sep 2005",slug:"/2005-09-03-emergency-aid-for-katrina-at-the-german-red-cross/"}}},{node:{fields:{title:"Wahl-O-Mat",date:"26 Aug 2005",slug:"/2005-08-26-wahl-o-mat/",tags:"Y2005"},html:'<p>I can\'t vote in the Bundestag election next month, and judging from the <a href="http://www.wahlomat.de/" title="Wahl-O-Mat">Wahl-O-Mat</a> I think most Germans are happy with that.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.wahlomat.de/" title="Wahl-O-Mat: Green 64%, FDP 63%"><img src="http://www.papascott.de/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2005/08/wahlomat2005.png" border="1" height="314" width="474" alt="wahlomat2005.png" /></a></p>\n<p>I\'ve said before I wish I could vote for a <a href="http://www.papascott.de/archives/2004/03/15/tobias-is-looking-for-a-german-greenish-kind-of-liberal-new-labour-party/">German greenish kind of liberal New Labour party</a>, and this just proves it. <a href="http://www.couchblog.de/webpropaganda/article/960/quod-erat-demonstrandum" title="Webpropaganda: Quod erat demonstrandum">(via Webpropaganda, among others)</a></p>'},next:{fields:{title:"PawSense",date:"24 Aug 2005",slug:"/2005-08-24-pawsense/"}},previous:{fields:{title:"Mac in Mac",date:"27 Aug 2005",slug:"/2005-08-27-mac-in-mac/"}}}],pathPrefix:"",first:!1,last:!1,index:286,pageCount:1101}}}});
//# sourceMappingURL=path---286-333d84b400b9bde827c9.js.map